<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1804" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Harpalus (Harpalus) atratus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" subGenus="Harpalus">Harpalus (Harpalus) atratus (Latreille, 1804)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Europe (except the north) and the Balkans, where it prefers foothills to alpine regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Arndt, E." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Ground Beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
It is a mesoxerophilous and polyphagous species, which prefers to live in forested areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Varvara, M." journalOrPublisher="Analele Stiintifice ale Universitatii &quot; AI. I. Cuza &quot; Iasi, s. Biologie Animala" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="1 - 9" title="Diversity and the Main Ecological Requirements of the Epigeic Species of Carabidae (Coleoptera, Carabidae) in the Sun Flower Ecosystem, Broscauti (Botosani County)." volume="LIV" year="2008">Varvara and Apostol 2008</bibRefCitation>
). It feeds on a mixture of seeds from agricultural crops, weeds and shrub species (
<bibRefCitation author="Lundgren, J." journalOrPublisher="Progress in Biological Control" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="143 - 165" title="Relationships of Natural Enemies and Non-Prey Foods" volume="7" year="2009">Lundgren 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, it was only found in the wheat field in the homogeneous area (n = 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
